{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01BMo1WabDNVtfCc5ey7vSHG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me look at how the deepcopy is generated for IstioCSRConfig to understand what the new field's deepcopy will look like (it's a simple string, so no special deepcopy needed).\n\nLet me also check the existing immutability pattern used in the codebase. Looking at `IstiodTLSConfig`:\n\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"!has(oldSelf.privateKeyAlgorithm) && !has(self.privateKeyAlgorithm) || has(oldSelf.privateKeyAlgorithm) && has(self.privateKeyAlgorithm)\",message=\"privateKeyAlgorithm may only be configured during creation\"\n```\n\nThis enforces presence immutability for optional fields - once set, it can't be removed; once unset, it can't be added. There's also a value-immutability rule that prevents changing the value once it's been set.\n\nSo I need to add a `TLSMinVersion` field to `IstioCSRConfig` with enum constraints for `VersionTLS12` and `VersionTLS13`.\n\nThen I'll need to update the `updateArgList` function in deployments.go to pass the `--tls-min-version` flag when this field is configured.\n\nLooking at how `IstiodTLSConfig` implements its type-level presence-immutability rule, I need to add something similar to `IstioCSRConfig` since it doesn't currently have any XValidation rules at the type level.\n\nWriting validation rules...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1340,"cache_read_input_tokens":51113,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1340,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09f1e293-33ec-4a3a-90a4-e6b51e0146dd","uuid":"5c6a430b-9096-468a-9ed3-39a9570babe6","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:41:08.616Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDijPXkYMzLE1v1Xu7m